Product name: Vintage rare Sugalite carved Quan Yin pendant. (pdgm125)
Description:
A pendant carved from Sugilite in the form of a graceful Quan Yin. This mini treasure is of the finest color deep (Welch’s Concord Grape Juice saturation) – a true unctuous purple. This piece is of Chinese Master Carver caliber and perfectly conveys the spirit of Quan Yin, the embodiment of compassion, mercy and kindness. Both front and reverse are different but in keeping with the theme. The design wraps entirely around the carving.
Sugilite Is a rare purple mineral that was first discovered in 1944. This material was not suitable for ornamentation and it was not until 1979 when it was re-discovered in the Southern Kalahari Desert of South Africa. In 1980 Sugilite was classified as a rare gem, which, according to supply and demand economics, resulted in a price increase. And into the next century, today prices are commensurate with the extreme rarity.
Sugilite gets its attractive purple color from traces of Manganese. It can range inn color from pinkish purple to deep bluish-purple. The most highly valued Sugilite gemstones are a uniform intense purple. A great deal of Sugilite has patches, veins or layers. This carving is the rarer intense purple variety and priced accordingly.
Circa: 1970's
Measurement: 1-1/2 x 1 x 3/16 inches
Weight: 6 grams
Source: South Africa
Carving: Chinese

Product name: Vintage Nautical Sea Map Gallipoli Pull Down Map 1979 Made in Turkey 1970's Sea Sailing Map Geography
Description:
A gorgeous genuine vintage nautical sea map printed in 1979, with small hand modifications made in 1980 and 1981, in Turkey showing a small part of the west coast of Turkey. The main focus is on Gökçe island and its surrounding which is the famous Gallipoli peninsula and the islands near by. Gallipoli was heavily attacked for 8 months during WW1 as it was the way to get to Constantinople (modern Istanbul) , which was the capital of the Ottoman Empire (the Turkish republic was established 8 years after this).
The Gallipoli Campain, or in Turkish Çanakkale savaşı, is a defining moment of it's nation's history. Read more about it at Wikipedia:
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gallipoli_Campaign
The map is big and beautifully colored and will look amazing in any room.
A perfect gift for map, globe, geography lovers, sailors, sea lovers, teachers and collectors, maps gives so much character to a house
It rolls by hand on wooden dowels.
All text is in Turkish and English, and it shows the depths of the sea in meters.
scale 1: 100.000
Condition: Good vintage condition, some yellowing due to its 35 years on the world and a few water stains.
Measurements: 
height: 42'' (106 cm)
width: 29 1/2'' (75 cm) with the wooden sticks it is 36'' (91.5 cm)

The Depression Journal is designed to provide encouragement, recognition & love to those who struggle with depressed feelings.

~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
HOW TO BUILD-YOUR-OWN THERAPY JOURNAL
1. You start by purchasing the Therapy Journal for Mental Health Struggles, which is the most thorough journal in the shop. It includes 33 pages which are designed to provide encouragement, recognition & love to those who are struggling with a mental health issue or general life struggle. Click the link below for a full description and list of pages:
https://www.etsy.com/listing/265606248/therapy-journal-for-mental-health
2. Then you can customize your journal by purchasing additional topic-specific journals, such as Depression, Eating Disorders, Personality Disorders, Grief, Self-Harm, Skin Picking & more. These journals are organized in the Category section of my shop.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
**PLEASE READ**
This is an Instant Digital Download - you will not receive anything in the mail. Upon your purchase, you will immediately receive a link to download a zip file containing a total of 12 unique pages. 
FORMAT/SIZE
This Journal is standard US Letter Size (8.5 x 11 inches) and is in PDF format, so you will need to be able to open PDF documents on your computer. Adobe Acrobat is a free software program that allows you to open PDF documents. Copy & paste the link below onto your URL browser to download Adobe Acrobat:
https://get.adobe.com/reader/
PRINTING
This Journal is standard US Letter Size and should be printed on standard US Letter Size Paper. When printing, make sure the paper size is set to Us Letter, and make sure to scale to 100% (don't scale to fit page). 
On the Portrait-oriented pages, there is a .6 inch margin on the left/right side so you will have room to hole punch. On the Landscape-oriented pages, the .6 margins are on the top/bottom. 
TERMS OF USE
This Journal is copyrighted and is intended for personal use only. You can reprint pages as many times as you’d like, as long as they are for your personal use. Please do not resell or redistribute to others. 
REFUNDS
I cannot offer refunds on digital files. Once I send you the files, the sale is final. But I can and will do everything possible to make sure you are happy with your order. If you have any problems, I will work with you until I resolve the issue.

DISCLAIMER:
I, Katie Rushing, the creator of Therapy Journals, am not a licensed therapist, psychiatrist, nurse, doctor, dietician or mental health worker, nor am I claiming to heal, cure, prevent or treat any medical/emotional/mental conditions. 
My shop is designed to provide encouragement, comfort, recognition and love to those who struggle with any type of mental health issue. 
PLEASE NOTE: Many mental health illnesses can involve intense/distressing memories and feelings. Journaling may not be suitable for everyone. It is always wise to check with your doctor or therapist before journaling. 
Each journal contains different types of pages, none of which are providing medical advice. The different types of pages are:
- Tracking/Logging: These pages are set up as blank charts/tables/spreadsheets for the purpose of tracking certain behaviors, thoughts & emotions, and recording potential growth.
- Lists: These pages contain comprehensive lists (example: emotions, thoughts, activities) and can be used as a reference sheet. 
- Guided Journaling: These pages contain questions/prompts for those who benefit from daily writing.   
- Encouragement: These sheets are designed to encourage, such as “15 ways to love your body,” and are not meant to be received as medical advice. 
The reason I created Therapy Journals is because I have spent many years in therapy for Depression, and I have been through intensive residential treatment for Bulimia, and I have developed a strong passion for those who suffer from a mental health illness. Journaling has been a very helpful tool for me, and I want to share that resource with others.

Product name: Fresh Bitten Pineapple Sugar Scrub - Pineapple Sugar Scrub - Tropical Sugar Scrub
Description:
This glorious sweet fragrance is toned down beautifully by the addition of an unlikely herb: cilantro. Ripe pineapple juices are complemented with coconut shavings, bursting orange notes and sparkling cilantro. Warm vanilla and mists of musk complete this zesty aroma!
What is the difference between a regular scrub and an emulsified scrub? A regular scrub contains just a material to exfoliant, like sugar or salt, sitting in a pool of oils. It tends to separate in the jar, dry out, and can leave your skin feeling extra greasy because they don't absorb into the skin. On the other hand, EMULSIFIED scrubs are a creamy, ice cream like consistency that is thickened with an emulsifying wax, and has butters, oils, and nutrients that absorb into the skin, all while the sugar removes dead skin to leave your skin heavenly soft. This scrub is never greasy, and helps make the skin glow and rejuvenate it to make your skin plump and healthy.
How to Use: Use a spoon, stick, or other small utensil (I try to include in orders) to place a small amount on the desired, damp area of skin. Gently rub in circular motions to remove the dead skin and work the oils and butters into your skin. Rinse off with warm water and enjoy!

This Activated Charcoal handmade soap is my best selling soap and here's why - my charcoal soap contains activated charcoal in addition to a combination of essential oils wonderful for any skin type, not drying just soothing. Makes a wonderful facial soap and a great all over body bar.
This listing is for 1 bar of soap, each bar weighs between 4.7 - 5.4 ounces.

~ Detergent Free ~

Our palm oil supplier is a member of the Roundtable on Sustainable Palm Oil (RSPO), an organization that supports sustainable palm oil production.
TESTIMONIALS
*****************************
Really surprised with this face cleanser, I have combination skin (quite oily and quite dry)- and it makes for a difficult time finding a good cleanser to clear out my pores without over drying my skin (which then makes me over produce oil and break out). 
My face felt clean but not sucked of all the natural oils.
Unbelievably fast shipping! I love this soap too, it's one of my favorite face soaps ever and I've used a ton - including the really expensive brands.
Highly recommend!! I first came across it in this store, and it's fantastic!!! Thank you Melissa!!!
"I use this soap on my face and it is awesome. It smells great. I feel like I'm at a spa when I use it. It lathers well and my face feels really clean when I rinse it off.
This soap is perfect. I use it all over. It moisturizes even better than the sea salt soaps.
This soap is amazing! I've never used anything like it. And customer service/shipping was great.
L-O-V-E this soap! It smells great. Very generous size that should last me quite a while. Thanks so much - I'll definitely be back for more!
This formula is just awesome. I have a very sensitive irritated mixed combination skin but I do NOT have any problems at all using this soap!!! Thanks
This is my 5th purchase from Melissa in the last year and my first time trying out a few different soaps. I really like the activated charcoal, it has a nice, clean, smell and dries out my skin in a good way. Three Kings smells like cinnamon and spice and everything nice. The other bars that I ordered (rosemary and lavender mixes) smell very herbal, a bit overwhelmingly so. That's probably fine if you like herbs and aromatherapy. I do have to say, Melissa makes the BEST lip balms. (Peppermint ice and lavender mint = amazing) I have been using her lip balms exclusively for the last year and they last forever. :)
This soap is fantastic. It smells refreshing and invigorating, and it feels positively wonderful on your skin. I'm so happy I purchased this. It will definitely become a staple in my soap collection.
Wow... what a wonderful experience.... ordering more
I love this product so far!

Product name: You Can Do Anything Personalized CD - Your Child's Name Used 106 Xs in This Lively & Fun CD.  Songs that'll make you want to dance
Description:
The "You Can Do Anything" CD is lively, upbeat and has a positive message.  The songs are fun-loving and encourage the child to sing and dance along. Check out the track listing below.
1. You Can Do Anything
2. Way Too Much To Do
3. Simon Says
4. If They Put You In Charge Of The Zoo
5. All Because Of You
6. In Your Own Backyard
7. Junk Food Flavored Healthy Veggie Treats
8. Tomorrow
I love the positive message of this CD. If you were watching this CD for Adam, some of the lyrics in the first song are, "You can do anything that you can dream, Adam, run and climb, just laugh and smile and sing, Adam. We can do anything, so come with me. We'll learn to be brave; we'll grow to be strong, together as friends we'll travel along....come on!! You can do anything that you can dream, Adam....."
The track of Simon Says is really cute. It's like the game of Simon says, but the child's name has to be sung in the track instead of Simon. This track will have your child on their feet dancing right along as their name is used over and over. The song says, "Remember, only do the actions when you hear your name".
Consider a personalized CD for your next birthday gift, or Christmas or just anytime you want to bless that special child in your life. Remember, gifts like this won't be found at any of the retail toy stores, or discount houses. This will be a unique gift, something they'll treasure always.
To find your child's name, look at the list below. If you can't find the name you’re looking for, look under different spelling choices. If you find the name you're looking for, but it's not spelled correctly, that’s no problem. I make each CD when it's ordered, so I'll make sure to spell it correctly on the label. You can also add a personalized message on the label. If you want to make the CD a keepsake, make sure to fill out the message line when you order. It can be up to 3 lines long.

Product name: French purple books Classiques Larousse decorative softback books with FREE SHIPPING
Description:
A Classiques Larousse paperback book with the iconic purple paper covers. I have a large selection of classic French literature available by Moliere, Corneille, Pascal, Descartes etc. These lovely books are so decorative, they would add charm to your photos, a touch of French character to your home decor or could be used in your altered art projects. Equally they would be a great addition to any vintage book collection. 
Please select the title(s) you require from the options menu
These books are in vintage condition. They have foxing on the pages and the covers have that wonderful beige patina that these old paperbacks acquire over time. The edges of the pages have a wonderful deep tanning. There is some underlining and writing, pencil marks, ink blots etc Some have a name written or stamped on the front and inside covers.
These books measure approximately 4 1/4 inches wide x 7 inches tall (approx 11 x 17.5cm)
FREE SHIPPING to international destinations on these books with the "livres et brochures" service from France. I'm afraid the free shipping is not available to customers in France. Please allow up to 4 weeks for delivery. If you would like quicker shipping I can send them letter post at an extra charge, just convo me for the cost.
To see more vintage French books and collectibles please visit my shop, Histoires

Product name: Candle Dye 1 Oz Liquid Candle Color, Candle Wax Dye, Sample Set, Black, Blue, Green, Ivory, Pink, Purple, Red, Yellow
Description:
Liquid candle dye in easy to use dropper bottles. Eight vibrant colors: black, blue, green, ivory, pink, purple, red and yellow available in 1 oz. bottles. Sample set contains 5 ml. bottles in 5 colors: blue, green, purple, red and yellow. Photos show samples of colors in different wax types using an average of 2-6 drops per pound. Use more or less of a color or blend different colors for endless possibilities. Fragrance oils vary in color; some are clear, yellow, tan etc.; so please make notes in your formulations of variations as you test. 
Approved for use with all types of wax including palm, paraffin, soy and blends. Used for creating candles, wax melts / tarts and aroma beads. 
Select quantity from drop menu along with your choice of 1 ounce (30 ml) color selection or 5 ml color sample set. All are packaged in amber glass bottles with dropper tops. 
Each of the 5 sample bottles in the set contains 5 ml of liquid dye x 5 colors for a total of 25 ml (0 .8 oz). 5 ml conversions = 1/6th oz = 1 teaspoon = 100 drops. Most folks choose the sample set to start with since 1 ounce of color tints approximately 100 pounds of wax; that's a lot of candles. 
 IMPORTANT NOTES:
* To order the sample set select Size '5 ml' and 'Rainbow' color.
* Store in cool environment away from direct sunlight and out of reach of children and pets. Shake before use.
* Protect your work area!! Dye may stain surfaces. Wear gloves or wash ASAP for skin contact.
* Add color after wax has reached recommended melt temperature and before pour temperature; so basically the same time you add fragrance oil. 
* Expect color changes as wax cools. Most dry to lighter shades.
* Ingredients in colorants are protected by proprietary laws. We suspect they are oil based since they're a bit smelly and can mix with wax, thus oils. No worries about the smell impacting your finished candles as it's a tiny percentage of the formulation. 
******************************************************************
FAQ (Frequently Asked Questions)
Q: Can I select different colors in the sample set?
A: Sorry, no. These are pre-packed for quick process & shipping. Set includes blue, green, purple, red & yellow. 
Q: Do you discount for multiple quantities?
A: Yes. Order 10 or more items from our ‘Craft Supply DIY’ section to receive 20% off list price for all locations. All 10 do not have to be the same, okay to select all different to get to the discounted volume of units. Listings sold as sets count as 1 item. Click on this link to shop items that qualify. 
https://www.etsy.com/shop/CountryFolkSoap/items?ref=hdr_shop_menu§ion_id=10494060
Once 10 or more items are in your cart enter coupon code SUPPLY20 during checkout for instant savings. Orders not meeting the qualifying 10 items will be cancelled. 
Q: Do you have other colors available?
A: Sorry, No. We only stock colors we use. 
Q: What's the difference in liquid VS colored wax chips?
A: Liquid is MUCH EASIER to produce consistent color in your wax recipes by controlling amount of drops added per pound. Wax chips need to be cut and weighed, not easy to do unless you have a scale that measures in grams for small batches or pastel colors. We make lots of candles and much happier with liquid dye.
Q: Can I use powdered dye?
A: Only if candles are for decorative purposes!!! Powdered dye is combustible, NOT recommended for candles you intend to burn.
Q: Can I use these for other applications like clay, soap, etc.?
A: We cannot provide additional details for use in crafting outside our area of expertise. We also make soap, but honestly never tried using these as we  have other options approved for soap use. 
See other candle supplies available including containers, fragrance oils, labels, wicks and more.

Product name: Beech Wood Sajou Lace Bobbins
Description:
Beautiful Beech wood lace bobbins from Sajou.
Available in packs of six or twelve, these bobbins measure 9.8 cm long and 11 mm diameter
Sajou produce haberdashery items made  in France to the highest standards (in some cases even produced on the original old machinery). Perfect for gifts and collectors, and for those of you unable to resist a quality that is seldom found in today's mass produced haberdashery products.
Sajou was created in 1828 by Jaques- Simon Sajou, selling haberdashery for embroidery, tapestry, lace, crochet and weaving. His pattern albums are sought after to this day by collectors worldwide. In 2005 the Sajou brand was purchased and revived by avid collector; Frederique Crestin- Billet. Many of the old designs have been faithfully reproduced and there are some new designs that have been added in the Sajou style.  
I have other Sajou haberdashery items for sale in my shop so please do take the time to have a browse.

Product name: Mini DIY Farmers' Cheese Kit- 3-5 batches (cow milk)
Description:
It may be teenie* but this Mini Farmers’ Cheese Kit is packed with fun and cheesy possibilities.  This cheese is fittingly rustic and very adaptable. It can vary from ricotta to feta in flavor and texture. You can use it creamy, firm, sweet or savory - the instructions will guide you! 
KIT INCLUDES: 
 - Instructions with Tips and Variations
 - Unlimited Email Support as Needed
 - Fine Mesh, 100% Cotton Cheesecloth also known as Butter Muslin
 - Gluten-free, Non-GMO Citric Acid
 - Pure, Non-Iodized Flake Salt
WHAT YOU NEED:
Simply add milk and in under an hour you will be eating and sharing your very own fresh cheese! No aging required!  Pasteurized store-bought or raw farm-fresh milk both work.  Make sure your store bought milk is not ultra-pasteurized or UHT, ultra-heat pasteurized. 
DIETARY GUIDELINES:
The Mini Farmers’ Cheese Kit is gluten-free, Non-GMO and vegetarian friendly.
QUANTITY:
The Mini Farmers Cheese Kit makes 3 batches of cheese. A batch is about 1 lb so you will have plenty of supplies to try your hand at not only making the cheese but experimenting with different flavors, shapes and recipes. Use bowls, cupcake tins etc. as molds at home.
GOOD TO KNOW:
One of the many unique characteristics of this cheese is that it doesn't melt, so you can actually pan-fry cubes for a browned, crispy, chewy, crazy good treat. Use it instead of croutons on a crisp green salad, fry it like an egg for an amazing sandwich, replace meat or tofu in any dish or just dip cubes as appetizers in a delicious sauce (BBQ, plum, pesto, salsa...) You can make a veggie dip, ricotta cheesecake, mix with jam and top pancakes, use it savory to fill pasta shells, dollop onto chili, layer in lasagna, or crumble onto salads like feta.
The possibilities are endless!
FOOD SAFETY AND HANDLING: 
The kits and supplies are hand-poured, hand-folded and assembled in a food-safe, fully-licensed facilities that strictly follow the Department of Agriculture cleaning guidelines. The food items are all gluten-free but packaged in a room that may come in contact with wheat, soy, corn, nuts and other food allergens.  
SHELF LIFE for the Mini Farmers’ Cheese Kit is 5 years. 
For more information visit www.urbancheesecraft.com
